replyContent: Hi Mariann, good news! Yes, you can change between right and left handed. On the game selection screen, tap any of the four "suit" icons in the top-right corner (under the game name). You can choose from 4 different layouts for each game. :)

content: What ever I don't keep my tablet online it's a pain I cant play with out big brother making sure I paid.
replyContent: No worries, you saw a message simply because it didn't make an online connection the first time you ran it. It's the standard license check supplied by Google for paid apps, and it will remember. You don't have to be online each time you run the app.  :)

content: I've tried them all and this is the best one I've seen yet.  In fact, I ended up buying three copies, one for me, my mom and my dad.  We couldn't be happier.  Definitely money well spent.
replyContent: Three happy customers makes for a happy developer. :) Enjoy the games!

content: Beautiful graphics,  spectacular animations, and all the best solitaire games are right here in Solitaire Planet. What first amazed me is that it has all of my favorite solitaire games. This includes putt putt and Monte Carlo which are often not found in other game collections. The cards are big, gorgeous, and easy to read. It keeps track of your stats and even includes a place for your favorites for quick selection. I highly recommend this for all solitaire lovers like me out there.
Simply the best solitaire app on the market, can't stop playing!
Loving this game

The best solitaire app in the store.  The amount of different games you can try is unbelievable. Excellent coding and ui is liquid smooth.   Highly recomend, worth the price.
